Eighty people have been injured after two buses collided on the Mangosuthu Highway in Umlazi in KwaZulu Natal on Wednesday.Emergency services(ER24) paramedics and other services arrived at the scene to find two buses collided and with the passengers either on the side of the road or still getting of the bus.&#8220;Numerous occupants were found seated on the side of the road while some occupants were found climbing out of the vehicle,&#8221; said ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring.No serious injuries have been reported however a number of people are in hospital for further examination.&#8220;The cause of the collision is not yet known but local authorities are on scene for further investigations&#8221;, said Meiring.&nbsp;-Aviwe Maxheke